result.execSummary:
The defendant Terrance F Williams was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • First Degree Child Sexual Assault-Contact With A Child Under Age 13, a class B felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.02(1)(e).
  • Repeated Sexual Assault of Same Child, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.025(1)(e).
  • Second Degree Sexual Assault of Child (<16 Years of Age), a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.02(2).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Pre-sentence investigation and Defense Sentencing Memorandum have been received and reviewed by Court and parties. Corrections/ additions addressed on the record.

AS TO COUNT 2 : The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 20 YEARS; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 10 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 10 YEARS; concurrent with all other counts; with credit of 440 days time served.

AS TO COUNT 3 : The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 16 YEARS; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 8 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 8 YEARS; concurrent with all other counts; with credit of 440 days time served.

AS TO COUNT 6 : The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 16 YEARS; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 8 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 8 YEARS; concurrent with all other counts; with credit of 440 days time served.

Court finds defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration program or the WI Substance Abuse program.  

AS TO COUNT 7: Court ordered defendant to serve 90 DAYS in the House of Correction concurrent with all other counts; with credit for 440 days time served. 


Court ordered alcohol and drug assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.

Defendant Terrance F Williams in court with attorney Jeffrey William Jensen.  Defendant Terrance F Williams in custody.  Taylor L. Kraus appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case in court for jury trial. Parties have reached a resolution.Plea hearing held.  

Defendant changes plea to GUILTY as to COUNTS 2 & 3 and AMENDED COUNTS 6 & 7.

Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court orders COUNTS 1, 4, & 5 DISMISSED and READ-IN for sentencing purposes.  

Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.  Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Plea questionnaire, addendum and jury instructions received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Defendant is advised he is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms.  Defendant is advised he is unable to vote in any election until civil rights are restored.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  PSI without recommendation was ordered with a psychosexual evaluation.  Court orders defendant REMANDED to the custody of the Sheriff pending sentencing hearing. Case adjourned for sentencing hearing.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for August 23, 2019 at 08:30 am.
